The frontend is in htmx. Styling is done in CSS. Find the style sheet in src/static/style.css.

Page templates are stored in src/templates. This has a subfolder partials that stores templates for parts of the page (e.g. forms).

Navigation can be done from the home page and the navbar. the navigation options should be equal. There are sections that contain links to pages. The layout is slightly different:
- home page sections contains tiles with explanation; tiles can be clicked
- navbar sections are buttons with dropdowns with buttons inside; the inner buttons can be clicked

### Reuse CSS classes before creating new ones
1. Before adding a class, search `src/static/style.css` and `src/templates/` for an existing class with the same role (link, chip, form row, color picker, inline confirm, etc.).
2. Prefer semantic, reusable classes (`recipe-link`, `tag-group-chip`, `manage-shop-color-input`) over page-prefixed ones (`week-menu-recipe-link`, `recipes-missing-tags-recipe-link`, `color-input`).
3. Use generic classes and avoid page-specific classes as much as possible; they are only for layout unique to that page (e.g. `recipes-missing-tags-list` as a container), not for styling common UI elements.
4. When copying UI from another page, copy the **same class names** from that page’s template — do not recreate the look with new CSS.